.TH "drm_hdmi_vendor_infoframe_from_display_mode" 9 "drm_hdmi_vendor_infoframe_from_display_mode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_hdmi_vendor_infoframe_from_display_mode \- fill an HDMI infoframe with data from a DRM display mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_hdmi_vendor_infoframe_from_display_mode
.BI "(struct hdmi_vendor_infoframe *frame "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_connector *connector "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_display_mode *mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "frame" 12
HDMI vendor infoframe
.IP "connector" 12
the connector
.IP "mode" 12
DRM display mode
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that there's is a need to send HDMI vendor infoframes only when using a
4k or stereoscopic 3D mode. So when giving any other mode as input this
function will return -EINVAL, error that can be safely ignored.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
